pyrbmi
Copyright 2026 StatParity

This product is a Python implementation of reference-based multiple imputation
methods originally developed in R.

Upstream References and Attributions:

1. rbmi (R package)
   Copyright: openpharma
   License: Apache-2.0
   Reference: Gower-Page C, et al. (2022). rbmi: A R package for standard and
   reference based multiple imputation. Journal of Open Source Software,
   7(78), 4251. https://doi.org/10.21105/joss.04251
   Repository: https://github.com/openpharma/rbmi

2. ICH E9(R1) Estimands Framework
   Source: International Council for Harmonisation of Technical Requirements
   for Pharmaceuticals for Human Use
   Reference: ICH E9(R1) (2019). Statistical Principles for Clinical Trials:
   Addendum on Estimands and Sensitivity Analysis. Step 4, November 2019.
   URL: https://www.ich.org/page/efficacy-guidelines

3. Multiple Imputation Theory
   Based on: Rubin DB (1987). Multiple Imputation for Nonresponse in Surveys.
   John Wiley & Sons.

This software maintains numerical parity with R's rbmi package for
regulatory submission workflows. Validation against R rbmi is performed
automatically via the test suite.

For the full list of dependencies and their licenses, see the package
documentation.
